topic.title: GPIO Multiplexing

note.p: Sourced from Trident GPIO Mux Issue 0.09: http://bby1dms01.pmc-sierra.internal/DocMgmt/fileinfo.cfm?file_id=427702
Also referenced to Trident RevA Digital IO Specification Issue 0.03: http://bby1dms01.pmc-sierra.internal/DocMgmt/fileinfo.cfm?file_id=437207

body.p: Many Switchtec peripheral functionalities are multiplexed with their GPIOs. This table describes how this multiplexing is implemented and configured in the Switchtec configuration file.

note.p: 1 3.3: Inputs are 3.3 V tolerant and outputs are open drain. These GPIOs will accept 1.8 V input levels but REQUIRE pull-ups when used as outputs
2 1.8: Inputs are 1.8 V tolerant only. Switchtec can drive 1.8V on these pins as an output.
3 These pins / functions are not available on the 29 mm x 29 mm package variants of Switchtec.
4 This TWI bus is used for BOOT ROM Firmware Recovery when the BOOT_RECOVERY pin is asserted.
5 This pin should be routed to a test point
6 Edge detection is not supported on GPIOs 16 to 19 and 68 to 74.
